Subject: [PATCH 3/3] COMP: Add Qt5::Widgets and Qt5::Xml to Cameras module

Cameras has no Widgets sublibrary, so Qt5 include dirs do not propagate
transitively through MODULE_TARGET_LIBRARIES.  SlicerMacroBuildLoadableModule
does not auto-add Qt5 targets, so CTK headers (e.g. ctkPimpl.h) that
include <QtGlobal> fail to compile.  Add Qt5::Widgets and Qt5::Xml
explicitly, matching the pattern used in SlicerMacroBuildModuleQtLibrary.
---
 Modules/Loadable/Cameras/CMakeLists.txt | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Modules/Loadable/Cameras/CMakeLists.txt b/Modules/Loadable/Cameras/CMakeLists.txt
index 3ad4fd857a..8fc8d24792 100644
--- a/Modules/Loadable/Cameras/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/Modules/Loadable/Cameras/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -45,6 +45,8 @@ set(MODULE_UI_SRCS
 
 set(MODULE_TARGET_LIBRARIES
   vtkSlicer${MODULE_NAME}ModuleLogic
+  Qt5::Widgets
+  Qt5::Xml
   )
 
 set(MODULE_RESOURCES
